2.2 Covariances

Load pre-computed covariance matrices (all chromosomes):

garm <- copdgene_garm()
arm <- copdgene_arm()

garm <- garm[ord, ord]
arm <- arm[ord, ord]

How are GARM/ARM computed?

copdgene_compute_garm
function()
{
  # inc
  stopifnot(requireNamespace("bigcov"))
  
  acs <- copdgene_acs(long = TRUE, clean = TRUE)
  
  garm <- bigcov::big_relmat(acs, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE, 
    num_splits = 100, verbose = 2)
  
  return(garm)
}
<environment: namespace:copdgene>
copdgene_compute_arm
function()
{
  # inc
  stopifnot(requireNamespace("bigcov"))
  
  acs <- copdgene_acs(long = TRUE, clean = TRUE)
  
  tacs <- t(acs)
  tacs <- scale(tacs, center = TRUE, scale = FALSE)
  acs <- t(tacs)
    
  arm <- bigcov::big_relmat(acs, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE, 
    num_splits = 100, verbose = 2)
  
  ids <- copdgene_ids_acs()
  rownames(arm) <- ids
  colnames(arm) <- ids
  
  return(arm)
}
<environment: namespace:copdgene>

The GARM/ARM matrices are partitioned on three small 50x50 blocks:

  • 1:50: low global (African) ancestry
  • 1501:1551: moderate global ancestry
  • 3201:3251: low global (African) ancestry
ind <- c(1:50, 1501:1551, 3201:3251)
m <- garm[ind, ind]
image(Matrix(m))

m2 <- m
m2[abs(m2) < 0.1] <- 0
image(Matrix(m2))

It seems that the diagonal entries are correlated with global ancestry.

plot(diag(garm), gacs)

The figures shows that individuals with high African ancestry has low variability across all their local ancestry segments.

3 Uncorrelated predictors

b <- 0

set.seed(1)

# data generation
X <- lapply(1:M, function(i) {
    p <- runif(1, 0.1, 0.9)
    q <- 1 - p
    
    sample(c(0, 1, 2), N, prob = c(p^2, 2 * p * q, q^2), replace = TRUE)
})
X <- do.call(cbind, X)

y <- rnorm(N)

# data scaling
X <- scale(X)
y <- scale(y)

3.1 Wald test

r <- as.numeric(crossprod(X, y))/N
s <- sqrt(N) * r
s2 <- s^2

pval_uncor_wald <- pchisq(s2, df = 1, lower = FALSE)
qq_plot(pval_uncor_wald)

3.2 Bootstrapping on the predictors

Sigma_S <- crossprod(X)/M
Sigma_S <- cov2cor(Sigma_S)

set.seed(1)
S_sim <- mvrnorm(L, rep(0, M), Sigma_S)
S_sim <- t(S_sim)

S2_sim <- S_sim^2

pval_uncor_bootpred <- sapply(1:M, function(i) (sum(S2_sim[i, ] > s2[i]) + 1)/(L + 
    1))
qq_plot(pval_uncor_bootpred)

3.3 Comparison

p1 <- data_frame(pval_uncor_wald = pval_uncor_wald, pval_uncor_bootpred = pval_uncor_bootpred) %>% 
    ggplot(aes(-log10(pval_uncor_wald), -log10(pval_uncor_bootpred))) + geom_point() + 
    geom_abline(linetype = 3) + coord_equal()

p1

R <- crossprod(X, Y)/N
S <- sqrt(N) * R
S2 <- S^2

pval_cor_bootout <- sapply(1:M, function(i) (sum(S2[i, ] > s2[i]) + 1)/(L + 
    1))
